15. Iubae tellus: Mauretania. The reference is probably to the younger Iuba, son of the king Iuba who killed himself after the defeat at Thapsus in 46 Bc. The young prince received a Roman education and was established on the throne This barren country (leonum arida nu- trix) was a poor return for the kingdom his father lost to the Romans.
